File: Oscar Pistorius looks on during the hearing in his murder trial at the High Court in Pretoria, on 6 July 2016. AFP/Marco Longari JOHANNESBURG - Convicted killer Oscar Pistorius has met the family of his former girlfriend, whom he shot dead nine years ago. He's trying to secure an early release from prison. READ: Oscar Pistorius to challenge parole delay The Justice and Correctional Services Department says the meeting is part of a Victim-Offender-Dialogue process. Pistorius has also been transferred back to the Atteridgeville Correctional Facility in Pretoria. READ: Pistorius to meet Steenkamp family In November last year, the former Paralympian was sent to a prison in Gqeberha in the Eastern Cape. This is for the purpose of the Victim-Offender-Dialogue. It is not yet clear when Pistorious’s parole hearing will take place.